        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 1:15PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles east of Boswell to 6 miles south of
Bennington. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Unger...                          Soper...
Boswell...                        Gay...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
